sv:property.sv:value: eXo Platform is an out-of-the-box social intranet solution. Rich collaboration features such as wikis, forums, calendars and documents are smartly integrated around activity streams, social networking and workspaces. It is carefully designed to instantly engage users. It runs within the trusted security of an enterprise platform and is highly customizable to adapt when your needs evolve.

eXo began as an open source project in 2002, as the industry's first Java portlet container. The eXo Project catalyzed a portal market dominated by a handful of very large vendors selling six-figure software and lock in. We opened the floodgates to choice in this market, and customers came.

Mashup technology empowers web developers to become agents of Service-Oriented Architecture (SOA) within an enterprise, creating situational applications that can solve many unique business problems. Integrating data from multiple web application sources facilitates service reuse, and allows for new and more meaningful interpretations.
